---
description: Client and worker runtime rules
globs: client/**/*.py
alwaysApply: false
---

# Client runtime

- Hard-fail missing `DATASET_PATH` unless `ALLOW_SYNTHETIC_DATA=true` (explicit opt-in only).
- Loaders live in `client/src/private_datasets/` (not empty `datasets/`).
- `MODEL_MODULE` dynamic import: hard-fail on error; never silently fall back to `simple_mlp` when custom was requested.
- Compute: only entrypoints allowed by `COMPUTE_PLUGIN_ALLOWLIST`.
- Prefer API keys in headers when adding new calls; avoid new query-string secrets.
- Do not send raw private dataset paths to public UI APIs.
